Hi there, 
I have recently installed your Eclipse Platform (as part of my new Linux Prof 
9.0 distribution) and experiencing some problems with it. In the "About 
Eclipse Platform" it identifes "Version: 2.1.1" and "Build id:200306271545". 
 
a) The following main problem I "half solved" by now, but I give you the 
details so you can follow what I detail in point b): when I first installed 
eclipse via Yast as root, I did not actually start the eclipse in /opt/eclipse 
but immediately logged in as user and run eclipse from there for the first 
time. It has given me the "Please wait ... Completing the Install" (twice I 
think) and finally started eclipse. To check whether the installation was 
successful, I checked in "Window -> Preferences" and it had only given me 
options "Workbench", "Help" and "Install/Update". Obviously, this installation 
was not useable. I found that after the Yast installation I have to start 
eclipse for the first time from within the root account, only afterwards then 
from the user account. However, this gives me the problems described below. 
 
b) This is what I get if I start the eclipse installation again from scratch: 
1.) installed eclipse via Yast in the root account 
2.) run "file:/opt/eclipse/eclipse" as root 
3.) "Please wait ... Completing the Install". The eclipse start-window does 
not start. Instead, a window pops up saying "Check the '.log' file in the 
'.metadata' directory of your workspace". The log-file is attached as 
root-log. At this point I could try several times again, but it would never 
start eclipse under root, but always come with the same, i.e. "Please wait ... 
Completing the Install" and then the "Check the '.log' file" 
4.) Logout as root, login as user and run "file:/opt/eclipse/eclipse" as user 
5.) "Please wait ... Completing the Install". After a while this disappears, 
then again "Please wait ... Completing the Install". 
6.) eclipse opens. 
7.) Checking the '.log' file in my users account, it lists errors (time 
10:35). The log-file is attached as user-log. 
8.) The problem described in a) is not present anymore. Checking "Window -> 
Preferences" seems to give me all options (ecpecially Java -> Installed JREs) 
9.) Open a new Java project, including a single java file to check whether it 
compiles and runs correct, then "Run as Java Application" -> perfect ! 
10.) Set breakpoint within java file, and select "Debug as Java Application" 
11.) Stays in Window "Progress Information" and says "Launching Rings", 
"Finding free socket" four about 4 minutes (is that normal ???). But I seem to 
be able to debug then. 
12.) Exit eclipse. Everytime I'm now starting eclipse again, it starts up with 
the "Please wait ... Completing the Install" again and not with the "normal" 
Start Window. It seems to show the same errors again (time 10:53), see 
attached user-log file. 
13.) I also attached "Help -> About Eclipse Platform -> Configuration Details" 
in the config-details file. 
 
Can you help ? I would very much appreciate if you are able to help me here. 
Thanks a lot in advance. 
 
Kind Regards 
Thomas Petermann
